  <chapter>
  	<title>Introduction</title>
	<para>
		The use of the template system is to cleanly seperate code and data.
	The data for the template system is stored in xml files. Their format is descriped 
	by DTDs which can be found in template/dtds. The XmlTemplate library is provided to
	allow it to access the data easily. It is based on libxml2 and gnome-vfs, both core
	components of the GNOME Desktop.
	</para>
  </chapter>
  <chapter>
  	<title>Using the Template System</title>
	<para>
		To use the template system you have to create an instance of the XmlTemplate
		class using xml_template_new(). The will scan the system for availible templates,
		they are stored in the PACKAGE_DATA_DIR"/template/ directory.
	</para>
  </chapter>
  <chapter>
	<title>Text Templates</title>
	<para>
		The most common template type is the text template. It provides simply text 
		parts which can be inserted in the editor, for example disclammers or comment
		blocks.
	</para>
	<para>
		There are multiple possibilities to get a text template. 
		xml_template_get_all_texts() privides a list of availible templates.
		With xml_template_get_text() you can get a specific text template by name and
		xml_template_query_by_language() gives a list of availible templates for a given
		language. Don't forget to free a template after usage.
	</para>
  </chapter>
